  "texts": [
    "Again, the generation process can use the information of the context and provide the link to the original document (e.g., a hyperlink to a document).",
    "Figure 2 provides an overview of what can be considered a plain vanilla RAG architecture.",
    "In addition, recent literature suggests several ways to improve the performance of a basic plain vanilla RAG architecture.",
    "For example, hierarchical information retrieval approaches allow for a deeper understanding and integration of information across documents, improving performance on complex, multi-step reasoning tasks.",
    "In particular, RAPTOR (Recursive Abstractive Processing for Tree-Organized Retrieval) recursively embeds, clusters, and summarizes text at multiple levels of abstraction (Sarthi et al. 2024)."
